tant;margin-left:0px !important;text-align:justify\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1;text-rendering:optimizelegibility;-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;font-weight:bolder\"><span style=\"font-family:ff-good-web-pro\"><strong>Factions</strong></span></span><span style=\"font-family:ff-good-web-pro\"> The Royal Family, The Arcane Congress, Nobles and Vassal Lords</span></p><hr style=\"box-sizing:content-box;line-height:1;text-rendering:optimizelegibility;-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;height:0px;overflow:visible;border-width:1px 0px;border-bottom-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.133);border-top-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.867);opacity:0.75;color:#222222;font-family:ff-good-web-pro;font-size:13.8667px;margin-top:0px !important;margin-right:0px !important;margin-left:0px !important;border-style:solid initial solid initial\" /><p class=\"hang\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1.4;text-rendering:optimizelegibility;-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;padding-left:1em;text-indent:-1em;color:#222222;font-family:ff-good-web-pro;font-size:13.8667px;margin-top:0px !important;margin-right:0px !important;margin-left:0px !important;text-align:justify\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1;text-rendering:optimizelegibility;-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;font-weight:bolder\"><span style=\"font-family:ff-good-web-pro\"><strong>Queen Aurala Ir'Wynarn</strong></span></span><span style=\"font-family:ff-good-web-pro\"> (NG female human) Queen of Aundair</span></p><p class=\"hang\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1.4;text-rendering:optimizelegibility;-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;padding-left:1em;text-indent:-1em;color:#222222;font-family:ff-good-web-pro;font-size:13.8667px;margin-top:0px !important;margin-right:0px !important;margin-left:0px !important;text-align:justify\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1;text-rendering:optimizelegibility;-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;font-weight:bolder\"><span style=\"font-family:ff-good-web-pro\"><strong>Adal Ir'Wynarn</strong></span></span><span style=\"font-family:ff-good-web-pro\"> (LN male human) Warlord and minister of magic, Aurala's brother</span></p><p class=\"hang\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1.4;text-rendering:optimizelegibility;-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;padding-left:1em;text-indent:-1em;color:#222222;font-family:ff-good-web-pro;font-size:13.8667px;margin-top:0px !important;margin-right:0px !important;margin-left:0px !important;text-align:justify\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1;text-rendering:optimizelegibility;-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;font-weight:bolder\"><span style=\"font-family:ff-good-web-pro\"><strong>Aurad Ir'Wynarn</strong></span></span><span style=\"font-family:ff-good-web-pro\"> (LG male human) Chief advisor and governor of Fairhaven, Aurala's brother</span></p><hr style=\"box-sizing:content-box;line-height:1;text-rendering:optimizelegibility;-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;height:0px;overflow:visible;border-width:1px 0px;border-bottom-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.133);border-top-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.867);opacity:0.75;color:#222222;font-family:ff-good-web-pro;font-size:13.8667px;margin-top:0px !important;margin-right:0px !important;margin-left:0px !important;border-style:solid initial solid initial\" /><p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1.4;text-rendering:optimizelegibility;-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;color:#222222;font-family:ff-good-web-pro;font-size:13.8667px;margin-top:0px !important;margin-right:0px !important;margin-left:0px !important;text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:ff-good-web-pro\">Aundair is one of the five nations of the original Kingdom of Galifar. Although much of its western forest territory has now become the Eldeen Reaches, Aundair still possesses beautiful swaths of fertile fields that supply the nations of Khorvaire with food and fine wines while large institutions of higher learning output scholars and knowledge.</span></p><p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1.4;text-rendering:optimizelegibility;-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;color:#222222;font-family:ff-good-web-pro;font-size:13.8667px;margin-top:0px !important;margin-right:0px !important;margin-left:0px !important;text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:ff-good-web-pro\"> </span></p><p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1.4;text-rendering:optimizelegibility;-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;color:#222222;font-family:ff-good-web-pro;font-size:13.8667px;margin-top:0px !important;margin-right:0px !important;margin-left:0px !important;text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:ff-good-web-pro\"><a href=\"https://eberron.fandom.com/wiki/Aundair\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Click here for more info on Aundair.</a></span></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":600000,"name":"Other Nations of Khorvaire","type":"image","_id":"ws8QpZQWUDAKjRQi","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{"caption":""},"text":{"format":1},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":"modules/pf2e-for-eberron/images/Khorvaire.png","system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":50000,"name":"The Five Nations","type":"text","_id":"fdYiUY2ouDlNWhPs","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<blockquote><p>The Five Nations are the five major human-dominated nations of Khorvaire, originating as the states that composed the Kingdom of Galifar from 1 YK to 894 YK and then independent kingdoms after the outbreak of the Last War. These are Aundair, Breland, Cyre, Karrnath, and Thrane.</p><p>The Five Nations were reduced to four with the destruction of Cyre and the creation of the Mournland. Although the Kingdom of Galifar no longer stands, each of the original five nations has remained, although slightly smaller than their original territories with new nations and regions being outlined as a result of the Last War.</p></blockquote><img src=\"modules/pf2e-for-eberron/images/TheFiveNations.png\" />","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":200000,"name":"Brelend","type":"text","_id":"ezaPBzT4Yile5k7R","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p class=\"hang\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1.4;text-rendering:optimizelegibility;-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;padding-left:1em;text-indent:-1em;color:#222222;font-family:ff-good-web-pro;font-size:13.8667px;margin-top:0px !important;margin-right:0px !important;margin-left:0px !important;text-align:justify\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1;text-rendering:optimizelegibility;-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;font-weight:bolder\"><span style=\"font-family:ff-good-web-pro\"><strong>Government</strong></span></span><span style=\"font-family:ff-good-web-pro\"> Constitutional Monarchy</span></p><p class=\"hang\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1.4;text-rendering:optimizelegibility;-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;padding-left:1em;text-indent:-1em;color:#222222;font-family:ff-good-web-pro;font-size:13.8667px;margin-top:0px !important;margin-right:0px !important;margin-left:0px !important;text-align:justify\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1;text-rendering:optimizelegibility;-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;font-weight:bolder\"><span styl