:0px;overflow:visible;border-width:1px 0px;border-bottom-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.133);border-top-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.867);opacity:0.75;color:#222222;font-family:ff-good-web-pro;font-size:13.8667px;margin-top:0px !important;margin-right:0px !important;margin-left:0px !important;border-style:solid initial solid initial\" /><p class=\"hang\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1.4;text-rendering:optimizelegibility;-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;padding-left:1em;text-indent:-1em;color:#222222;font-family:ff-good-web-pro;font-size:13.8667px;margin-top:0px !important;margin-right:0px !important;margin-left:0px !important;text-align:justify\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1;text-rendering:optimizelegibility;-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;font-weight:bolder\"><span style=\"font-family:ff-good-web-pro\"><strong>Vadallia</strong></span></span><span style=\"font-family:ff-good-web-pro\"> (N male elf) High King</span></p><hr style=\"box-sizing:content-box;line-height:1;text-rendering:optimizelegibility;-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;height:0px;overflow:visible;border-width:1px 0px;border-bottom-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.133);border-top-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.867);opacity:0.75;color:#222222;font-family:ff-good-web-pro;font-size:13.8667px;margin-top:0px !important;margin-right:0px !important;margin-left:0px !important;border-style:solid initial solid initial\" /><p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1.4;text-rendering:optimizelegibility;-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;color:#222222;font-family:ff-good-web-pro;font-size:13.8667px;margin-top:0px !important;margin-right:0px !important;margin-left:0px !important;text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:ff-good-web-pro\">For decades the elves fought on the side of Cyre, battling Talenta warbands, hobgoblin mercenaries, and the forces of Breland and Karrnath. They fought for the love of battle and gold, not loyalty to Cyre. Then, in 956 YK, the elves took action that surprised the Cyrans and the other Five Nations. War Leader Shaeras Vadallia proclaimed that his people had ties to the land from a time before human feet touched the soil of Khorvaire, and that his soldiers had restored those ties with spilled blood. Vadallia declared himself high king of the new nation of Valenar, and his warriors have been fortifying their position and slowly expanding their borders ever since.</span></p><p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1.4;text-rendering:optimizelegibility;-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;color:#222222;font-family:ff-good-web-pro;font-size:13.8667px;margin-top:0px !important;margin-right:0px !important;margin-left:0px !important;text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:ff-good-web-pro\"> </span></p><p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1.4;text-rendering:optimizelegibility;-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;color:#222222;font-family:ff-good-web-pro;font-size:13.8667px;margin-top:0px !important;margin-right:0px !important;margin-left:0px !important;text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:ff-good-web-pro\"><a href=\"https://eberron.fandom.com/wiki/Valenar\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Click here for more info on Valenar</a></span></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":1300000,"name":"Zilargo","type":"text","_id":"t2nx0VaNli1dwyjJ","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1;text-rendering:optimizelegibility;-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;font-weight:bolder\"><span style=\"font-family:ff-good-web-pro\"><strong>Government</strong></span></span><span style=\"font-family:ff-good-web-pro\"> Triumvirate</span></p><p c